I also encountered this bug in one of my apps. The patch below fixes many of these issues.

**Edit: patch 1 no longer works in latest master - it was deleted in favor of patch 2 below.**

The patch brought to light an invalid test case in the test suite (test/form/samples/recursive-calls/main.js). The relevant input:

```
$ cat removed6.js
const removed6 = {
        get x () {
                return globalVar ? removed6.x : () => {};
        }
};
removed6.x();
```
```
$ cat removed6.js | node
[stdin]:3
                return globalVar ? removed6.x : () => {};
                       ^

ReferenceError: globalVar is not defined
```
`rollup@1.2.2` incorrectly drops all the code in the example above despite the obvious side effects, but the patch correctly retains it as per the `node` run above.

The following patch variation has no test regressions (beyond that invalid test), however the third test case in the top post no longer works.

```patch
--- a/src/ast/nodes/CallExpression.ts
+++ b/src/ast/nodes/CallExpression.ts
@@ -17,6 +17,7 @@ import {
 } from '../utils/PathTracker';
 import { LiteralValueOrUnknown, UNKNOWN_EXPRESSION, UnknownValue } from '../values';
 import Identifier from './Identifier';
+import MemberExpression from './MemberExpression';
 import * as NodeType from './NodeType';
 import { ExpressionEntity } from './shared/Expression';
 import { ExpressionNode, INCLUDE_PARAMETERS, IncludeChildren, NodeBase } from './shared/Node';
@@ -66,6 +67,23 @@ export default class CallExpression extends NodeBase implements DeoptimizableEnt
                                this
                        );
                }
+               let v1, v2, v3, v4, v5, v6, v7, v8;
+               if (
+                       this.callee instanceof MemberExpression
+                       && this.callee.property instanceof Identifier
+                       && this.callee.object instanceof Identifier
+                       && (v1 = this.callee.object.variable)
+                       && (v2 = (v1 as any).init)
+                       && (v3 = (v2 as any).propertyMap)
+                       && (v4 = v3[this.callee.property.name])
+                       && (v5 = v4.exactMatchRead)
+                       && (v6 = v5.value)
+                       && (v7 = (v6 as any).body)
+                       && (v8 = (v7 as any).body)
+                       && (v8 as any).length
+               ) {
+                       this.callee.object.deoptimizePath(UNKNOWN_PATH);
+               }
                for (const argument of this.arguments) {
                        // This will make sure all properties of parameters behave as "unknown"
                        argument.deoptimizePath(UNKNOWN_PATH);
```

@lukastaegert Feel free to adapt the patches or ignore them. I don't plan to work on it further.

